# Birth Matching Registration Service

NOTE: This is a draft of the API and is subject to change

Birth Matching Registration Service is a service that allows you to check if the GRO for England and Wales contains a birth registration record for a given child.

## Group Birth Registration Match

## Check birth record exists for specific birth reference number [/birth-registration-matching/match]

Check for an existing birth record based on a birth reference number

+ birthReferenceNumber - unique 9 digit reference number found on birth certificate
+ firstName - childs forenames up to maximum of 4 values (space separated)
+ lastName - childs lastname
+ dateOfBirth - childs date of birth
+ whereBirthRegistered - where is the birth registered

+ Parameters
    + birthReferenceNumber: 123456789 (required, number)
    + firstName: John (required, string)
    + lastName:  Smith (required, string)
    + dateOfBirth: 2010-01-04 (required, string)
    + whereBirthRegistered: englandandwales (required, string)

### Check Birth [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

{
  "birthReferenceNumber": "123456789",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "dateOfBirth": "2014-05-18",
  "whereBirthRegistered": "englandandwales"
}

+ Headers
    API-Version: 1.0
    Origin: DFS

+ Response 200 (application/json)

{
  "matched": true
}

